excerpt: War memorial with tower & observation deck, built in 1936 originally to honour World War I sailors.
detail_description: The Naval Memorial, also known as the Laboe Naval Memorial, is a significant war memorial featuring a tower and observation deck. Originally built in 1936 to honor sailors of World War I, it now symbolizes all seafarers who lost their lives in both world wars. The towering structure offers a small exhibition on the ground floor and stunning panoramic views from its platform.
name: Naval Memorial

excerpt: Free-entry gardens organized by climate also featuring greenhouses with desert & tropical plants.
detail_description: Nestled within the Kiel University campus, the Botanical Garden is a stunning natural and cultural monument with a history dating back 350 years. This hidden gem boasts an impressive collection of approximately 14,000 plant species, making it an ideal spot for both scientific research and student training. The garden features greenhouses showcasing desert and tropical plants, offering visitors a captivating experience that seamlessly blends education, conservation, and breathtaking natural beauty.
name: Botanical Garden

detail_description: St. Nikolai Church in Kiel has a rich history, with its construction dating back to the city's founding in 1242. The church has undergone several reconstructions and extensions over the years, including a restoration after being devastated by Allied bomb raids during World War II. Despite the destruction, ecclesiastical treasures and artworks had been removed prior to the bombings. In 1950, the church was reconstructed using modern elements and materials.
name: St. Nikolai Church

excerpt: Kiel is a port city on Germany’s Baltic Sea coast. In the old town, the rebuilt, medieval St. Nikolai Church hosts classical concerts. Holstenstrasse and Dänische Strasse are streets lined with shops. Along the Kiel Fjord, the Maritime Museum displays model ships and nautical instruments in a former fish auction hall. Cruise ships dock at the Ostseekai Terminal in Germania Harbor.
detail_description: Kiel, a vibrant port city located on the Baltic Sea coast in Germany, offers a blend of historical charm and maritime attractions. The old town features the reconstructed St. Nikolai Church where classical concerts are held, while Holstenstrasse and Dänische Strasse boast an array of shops for visitors to explore. Along the picturesque Kiel Fjord, the Maritime Museum housed in a former fish auction hall showcases model ships and nautical instruments.
name: Kiel

excerpt: Boathouses & marinas line this waterfront drive with a bike lane & pedestrian promenade.
detail_description: Kiellinie is a picturesque waterfront drive along the Kiel Fjord, featuring boathouses, marinas, and a dedicated bike lane and pedestrian promenade. The route offers stunning views of the fjord and takes you past various attractions such as the Heimholtz Centre for Ocean Research with its outdoor seal aquarium. During Kiel Week, the promenade comes alive with concert stages and sailing races in the fjord.
name: Kiellinie

excerpt: 17th-century zoological museum with dinosaur skeletons & interactive exhibits in imposing building.
detail_description: The Zoological Museum of Kiel University is housed in an impressive 17th-century building designed by renowned architect Martin Gropius. Its collections, dating back to the 1600s, feature a remarkable exhibit in the main hall showcasing 13 suspended whale skeletons. The museum offers interactive displays on evolution and biodiversity, including marine life with a focus on whale species. Visitors can explore the latest marine research findings through 'The Future Ocean' exhibit.
name: Zoological Museum of Kiel University

detail_description: Kieler Brauerei am Alten Markt offers a rustic setting and a variety of culinary delights for the palate and senses. Visitors can savor German specialties in the brewery's cozy spaces and even pour their own beer at the table, immersing themselves in brewery culture while being surprised by the diverse beer selection. The brewery revives the tradition of small breweries and pubs that once thrived in the bustling harbor town, brewing craft beer since 1988.
name: Kieler Brauerei am Alten Markt

excerpt: Compact outdoor aquarium, best known for its seals, also exhibiting a variety of fish & crustaceans.
detail_description: Aquarium GEOMAR is a compact outdoor aquarium located in Kiel, offering a diverse range of marine life. It is best known for its seals and features various fish and crustaceans from the Baltic, Mediterranean, and tropical regions. The aquarium provides an immersive experience with lifelike environments showcasing Nordic and tropical swimmers. Visitors can explore the informative exhibits to learn about the diversity of marine creatures and their habitats.
name: Aquarium GEOMAR

excerpt: Kiel's maritime history is detailed through artifacts & models in this former municipal fish hall.
detail_description: The Kiel Maritime Museum, located in a former fish auction hall, offers a detailed look at the city's maritime history. The exhibits explore the significance of the harbor, navy, dockyards, and sailing through artifacts such as fishing boats, nautical instruments, and maritime-themed paintings. Additionally, visitors can admire a collection of antiques donated by a private collector. Nearby stands the reconstructed St.
name: Kiel Maritime Museum Fish Market & Museum Bridge

detail_description: Kieler Woche, also known as Kiel Week, is a major event in Germany that attracts between 600 and 800,000 visitors annually. The city of Kiel, also called 'the sailing city,' offers ample opportunities for maritime experiences. The Kieler Canal, the busiest of its kind globally, provides a unique view of giant ships. During the event, there are numerous attractions and around 100 dining options available.
name: Kieler Woche Marketing

excerpt: Popular park with a duck pond, playground & large, grassy field, with areas for picnics & BBQs.
detail_description: Schrevenpark is a beloved destination in Kiel, offering a serene atmosphere and various attractions for visitors. The park features a charming duck pond, expansive grassy fields ideal for picnics and barbecues, and well-maintained playgrounds for children. It is also known for hosting concerts during festive seasons. Visitors can relax by the water, observe waterfowl, or fly kites while adhering to summer grilling regulations.
name: Schrevenpark

excerpt: Historical & technical submarine museum housed in a German U-boat active in World War II.
detail_description: German submarine U-995 is a historical and technical museum located on Laboe beach, housed in a World War II-era U-boat. This Nazi Germany submarine was damaged in 1944 and later used by the Norwegian navy until the 1960s. Today, it offers visitors a glimpse into its tight interior, including the engine room, cabins, control stations, and torpedo tubes. It is one of the few remaining intact U-boats and sits next to the Laboe Naval Memorial.
name: German submarine U-995

excerpt:
Schilksee is a town on the Danish Wahld peninsula in the Kieler Förde. In 1959, the town was incorporated into the city of Kiel, therefore today sometimes named as Kiel-Schilksee.
The town is a popular vacation destination because of its beaches and houses several resorts. Wikipedia.
name: Schilksee

excerpt: Wildlife park with forest & grassland areas, plus animal enclosures housing deer, wild boar & bison.
detail_description: Tiergehege Tannenberg is the largest wildlife park in Kiel, covering a vast 40-hectare area. Visitors can enjoy spending time in nature and observing animals such as deer, wild boar, bison, and other European wildlife species up close. While the park does not offer facilities and prohibits animal feeding, it provides a beautiful natural environment for leisurely walks and picturesque experiences.
name: Tiergehege Tannenberg

detail_description: Kieler Stadt- und Schifffahrtsmuseum offers a unique experience where visitors can immerse themselves in the history of Kiel. The museum provides an opportunity to learn about the city's past and its maritime heritage. After enjoying a relaxing time with coffee or tea while watching cruise ships, one can explore the museum to delve into Kiel's rich maritime history. It is a popular destination for those interested in gaining insights into the city's past and its connection to shipping.
name: Kieler Stadt- und Schifffahrtsmuseum

detail_description: Schloßgarten is the starting point of the Kiellinie in its northeastern region. Visitors can indulge in delightful dining experiences at charming cafes and restaurants while admiring a small aquarium and observing the activities of sailing clubs.
name: Schloßgarten

detail_description: If you're looking for an exhilarating adventure, look no further than Final Escape - Live Escape Game Kiel. This captivating venue offers a unique experience where participants must solve intricate riddles to escape from locked rooms within a set time limit. Each room presents its own thrilling scenario, immersing you in a world of mystery and excitement. One standout option is the Magic School room, which has enchanted visitors with its clever puzzles and enchanting atmosphere reminiscent of beloved fantasy tales.
name: Final Escape - Live Escape Game Kiel

detail_description: Nestled in the heart of Kiel, TanTamar is a charming little restaurant that specializes in delightful Thai cuisine. With its cozy and family-friendly atmosphere, it's the perfect spot to escape the hustle and bustle of daily life for a relaxing evening. The menu boasts an impressive array of Asian dishes with a focus on authentic Thai flavors, including delicious vegetarian and vegan options. Guests can also enjoy a variety of refreshing cocktails alongside their meals.
name: TanTamar

excerpt: Domed theatre with a program of 360° films on astronomical & scientific themes, plus kids’ shows.
detail_description: Nestled within the University of Applied Sciences in Kiel, Mediendom is a captivating 360-degree planetarium theater that promises an immersive experience for visitors of all ages. This unique dome theater not only aims to spark children's curiosity about astronomy and science through engaging interactive sessions but also serves as a cultural hub. With its comfortable seating arranged in three circles, guests can recline and enjoy stunning visual displays while listening to live performances, such as the enchanting 'Music of the Stars' concert.
name: Mediendom

detail_description: Anschar Park, located in the Wik district of Kiel, Schleswig-Holstein, is a green space that was once the site of Anschar Hospital. The hospital complex consisted of nearly 20 buildings including the main block, pavilions, chapel, and more. Today, only a few original structures remain amidst new apartments and offices. St. Peter's Church is nearby. The main hospital building now houses an art attic while another clinic building is being demolished.
name: Anschar Park
